reviews_data.review_text: Ordered Cinnamon Crunch bagels on Monday night for Tuesday on the 19th Aug. No crunch they were slimy and wet even toasting didn’t help. They also were flat.  Very disappointed with Panera first time I’ve gotten bagels that were not perfect.

My food is always correct and the staff is super friendly, but never, never, never come here when you're in a hurry. I get Panera takes longer than your average fast food places, but the Harrisburg and Charlotte locations move A LOT faster.
Says they open at 6am was there a little after and no one ever took my order waited there til 605 very disappointed

Please don't waste your time
..this place is horrible. Food is never correct...microwave inside missing...its always something at this location

The food is always really good taste wise, but im just not getting what Im paying for. I ordered a tuna salad sandwich with extra of pretty much everything. I got my order with hardly a regular amount of tuna salad. Ive never had this happen before but if Im paying for extra, there should be extra. The bread was falling apart and half of the tuna salad i was given wasnt even on the sandwich and was instead in the wrapper, making a messy eating experience in my car.

The least you can do is give us  full bowl when paying for a bowl of soup! The second picture is supposedly a mango smoothie. Please train your staff on how to properly prepare the dishes!

reviews_data.review_text: You know those places that call you by name when you come in and really make you feel welcome? This is that place. I eat here for lunch every day that I work in Concord!
Parking is hard to get into at times but the foods good for a chain so it’s fine

Has to be the worst panera experience, ordered melted avocado chicken sandwich, the quantity inside the bread was really poor, the sauce was missing and other fillings were poorly added. It felt like a toast with some cheese.
The atmosphere with their gentle music is wonderful. Good for family hangouts or having a date. Their foods, snacks and drinks are so nice.

I visited Panera Bread yesterday around 6:30 PM with my son after spending four exhausting hours in urgent care. Both of us were feeling very ill, tired, and miserable, and I just wanted to grab some soup without exposing anyone to COVID. Unfortunately, when I arrived, all of the outside lights were off, making the store look closed.

I went to the drive-thru to confirm if they were still open and was told they were. I then asked the representative if the drive-thru light could be turned on so I could see the menu, but he flatly said “no.” When I asked if it was broken, he simply said, “I think so,” without offering any further explanation or apology. I explained that I was very sick and didn’t want to expose anyone inside, but would have to come in since I couldn’t see the menu. My concern was ignored, and no empathy or apology was offered.

When I mustered the strength to go inside (wearing a mask, of course), I noticed everything in the front was already put away, as if the store was closing soon. I placed my order on the tablet but had to call out to get an employee to come from the back just to get me a cup for my drink.

The worst part was seeing the same employee from the drive-thru—identifiable by his voice and orange shirt—filling a bowl of soup at the pick-up counter without wearing gloves. This lack of hygiene was shocking.

To add to the frustration, the screen notified me that my food was ready, but I couldn’t find my order anywhere. When I asked the girl at the counter, she told me the man behind her was still working on it. Why was I notified it was ready when it wasn’t? I was already feeling miserable and just wanted to leave. While the woman apologized, I still had to wait an additional 7 minutes for my food.

This was the worst customer service I’ve ever experienced at Panera Bread. From the lack of concern for my situation to poor hygiene practices and long wait times, this visit was unacceptable. I will never return to this location.
Consistent and friendly. One of the best fast casual places in the area.

reviews_data.review_text: Good, tasty food. But a lil pricey, especially due to the fact that they do not fill their sandwiches with meat. Wish they had more customers service. You come in and do the order by machine instead of talking to a human. Other than that, Panera Bread is decent eating for fast food.

I ordered a Turkey and cheese sandwich with nothing on it, I drove home nearly 15 minutes away from the Panera bread location I ordered from just to have mayonnaise on the sandwich. The sandwich was for my son and we all know how kids can be picky with certain condiments. I drove back to the Panera bread and requested for my sandwhich to be corrected. Daniel, the night time manager was SO HELPFUL, ACCOMODATING, UNDERSTANDING, and just exhibited a customer service standard that is so rare these days. He corrected my sandwhich, and gave me gift cards as well! I am truly happy! As a single mother who work so hard for everything, it is a pure joy to have someone just fix a mistake without push back! THANK YOU so much, you are appreciated and you made my day! -Ms Jo
Needs improvement. Drive thru very slow. Can’t see screens. Broken sign. Needs work and effort.

I ordered in the parking lot upon pulling up and my food was ready within a few minutes. Like literally soon as I completed my order and walked in the door! Superb! Great atmosphere and fresh food!

Update: Changed 5 stars to 4 stars because the portion of meat was very disappointing considering me ordering a whole sandwich and was only given the amount of protein for a half sandwich.
The Concord location offers a great experience, manager was really nice and helpful.
Delicious food,  the cashier wasn't friendly or helpful but it is post covid

Have been here a few times only cuz it's convenient(across the street from where I work). Have only used the drive through and I don't know why I keep doing it. I will put an online/app order early in the day, thinking the bread and pastries will be put aside and saved for my order later. NOPE!!! I always do a drive through pick up and it's has been absolutely HORRIBLE all 3 times. I'm done!! They are slow AF, my order is never complete, they are always sold out of something I ordered ahead of time. I order my stuff to be ready by 730pm, pull into the drive through lane at 735, pull up to the speaker at 750, the window at 758, and still sit there for another 5 or 10 min while they are still getting my order together that was supposed to be ready 30 min earlier....I like their salads, but after work from now on, I'm going next door to chick fil a....so long Paranera!!!

The cashier wears the same gloves to handle money and grab my pastry. She didn't use a prong or change gloves. It was Oct 21 at 5:15 pm.

When I was eating my chili, I saw her walk to the restroom in the same gloves. She then went back to the front area, grabbed the cleaning things, and went back to the restroom to clean it. Then she went back up front to take an order. I never saw her change her gloves!

Don't get pastries from there. I threw mine out.

This Panera has probably the worst service of any Panera I've been to. They are regularly out of staples such as bread, signature soups, and bagels. Their drive-thru is incredibly inconvenient, you are locked in and can not get out if they are out of what you want or running super slow. Which is normal for their drive-thru. If you need to go here, go in and eat there to ensure you get all of your food and in a timely manner.

I was extremely impressed with Daniel, the General Manager today. I watched him check every order, notify customers of their status and politely distribute food and drinks. It is very refreshing to see such a hard working leader!

I decided to try it out again starting yesterday - they forgot the bacon on my sandwich and were out of baguettes. It was annoying but I shrugged it off and decided to try again today. This time they didn't even alert me they were out of baguettes and just decided to give me chips. I had to go back through the drive thru again just for them to tell me that I could have an apple or chips - No apology for not warning me or anything. So that's unfortunately the last time I'll be visiting this location. The food is was too pricey for the service provided.

Please recognize this gentleman. He is certainly a superior employee and good for your business.

I visited Panera Bread yesterday around 6:30 PM with my son after spending four exhausting hours in urgent care. Both of us were feeling very ill, tired, and miserable, and I just wanted to grab some soup without exposing anyone to COVID. Unfortunately, when I arrived, all of the outside lights were off, making the store look closed.

I went to the drive-thru to confirm if they were still open and was told they were. I then asked the representative if the drive-thru light could be turned on so I could see the menu, but he flatly said “no.” When I asked if it was broken, he simply said, “I think so,” without offering any further explanation or apology. I explained that I was very sick and didn’t want to expose anyone inside, but would have to come in since I couldn’t see the menu. My concern was ignored, and no empathy or apology was offered.

When I mustered the strength to go inside (wearing a mask, of course), I noticed everything in the front was already put away, as if the store was closing soon. I placed my order on the tablet but had to call out to get an employee to come from the back just to get me a cup for my drink.

The worst part was seeing the same employee from the drive-thru—identifiable by his voice and orange shirt—filling a bowl of soup at the pick-up counter without wearing gloves. This lack of hygiene was shocking.

To add to the frustration, the screen notified me that my food was ready, but I couldn’t find my order anywhere. When I asked the girl at the counter, she told me the man behind her was still working on it. Why was I notified it was ready when it wasn’t? I was already feeling miserable and just wanted to leave. While the woman apologized, I still had to wait an additional 7 minutes for my food.

This was the worst customer service I’ve ever experienced at Panera Bread. From the lack of concern for my situation to poor hygiene practices and long wait times, this visit was unacceptable. I will never return to this location.

Had the smoke chicken avo sandwich. The only thing missing was that the chicken sandwich looks like we are having a shortage of chicken meat.

The cashier wears the same gloves to handle money and grab my pastry. She didn't use a prong or change gloves. It was Oct 21 at 5:15 pm.

When I was eating my chili, I saw her walk to the restroom in the same gloves. She then went back to the front area, grabbed the cleaning things, and went back to the restroom to clean it. Then she went back up front to take an order. I never saw her change her gloves!

Don't get pastries from there. I threw mine out.

This Panera has probably the worst service of any Panera I've been to. They are regularly out of staples such as bread, signature soups, and bagels. bad service. drive thru worker seemed like it was his second day. waited over 35 minutes for food and it still wasnt done right.

My favorite place!

Food is delicious and service is great

Probably won't go back to this location anytime soon. I was extremely impressed with Daniel, the General Manager today. I watched him check every order, notify customers of their status and politely distribute food and drinks. It is very refreshing to see such a hard working leader!
Low on bagels at 10am

I expected a little better from this restaurant - I used to come to Panera (different location) often and never had an issue.

I decided to try it out again starting yesterday - they forgot the bacon on my sandwich and were out of baguettes. It was annoying but I shrugged it off and decided to try again today. Delicious cold sandwich, baguette with chicken and wild rice soup for lunch. Quick service all around and a clean environment. Parking is a legitimate nightmare. Don't even try parking in the lot, just do the one behind the restaurant...it's much easier.

Place legit never gets my morning order right not once. Same girl works mornings and seems too incompetent to use a bagel slicer correctly. Got a chicken tomato spinach sandwich and got two morsels of chicken on it, ordered a steak egg and cheese sandwich and got no egg. not to mention how no matter what i ask they always for some reason toast my bagel when its always marked as untoasted. not even to mention how bitter and burnt the coffee is. please fire your whole morning staff as they seem to be completely illiterate. p.s. the most insane part is how bagels are consistently cut with one insanely thick slice and one paper thin slice.
What a rip off. They messed up every part of my to go order, and it was way overpriced for the tiny portions

I love Panera and have for years. The food is always amazing!!! The service is great. And the dining area is always clean. Quiet place for breakfast. A lot of choices I recommend eggs and chicken sandwiches.
I'm sorry, but it is too expensive for two containers of soup and fixings it was over 50 bucks. Crazy.

This is the second time that I’ve been stiffed by this Panera Bread location. They forgot the other half of my sandwich from my Pick 2 order. Always check your order when doing 2-Go with this location, 2 for 2 having missing items is terrible service.
Good coffee ☕️
Young man at the window was polite and helpful! His name is Connor!
It's brand new!! This lovely Panera is fantastic! The people are kind and professional. The food is great!

I’ve never been to a friendlier Panera. I am so sorry I didn’t get the managers name. He greeting us when we entered with a big smile, was more than helpful, and  gave us a very friendly send off, even opened the door for us.

the food was great!! my favorite was the grilled cheese sandwich with tomato soup
